James Abraham, Jos The President of Nigeria National League side, Mighty Jets of Jos, Alhaji Ismaila Mabo, has approved the appointment of Ado Ali Katyen as the new chairman of the club. Media officer of the club Mbum Ferdinand disclosed this in a statement in Jos on Saturday The statement read, “The president of the club also thanked the outgoing chairman, Alexander Noel Wukari, for his diligence and hard work in striving to uplift the standard of the club in the last four years and wished him well in his future endeavours. “Mr. Katyen’s tenure is expected to run from 26 October 2020 to 26 October 2024. “Wukari is expected to officially hand over the reign of affairs to the incoming chairman, Mr Katyen, on or before 26 October 2020.”